    <summary>Identity-aware VPN and proxy CLI for zero-trust remote access (Pangolin)</summary>
    <description>Pangolin CLI is the official command-line client for [Pangolin](https://pangolin.net/) — an identity-aware, self-hostable tunneled reverse proxy and mesh VPN built on WireGuard.

The CLI connects a machine to a Pangolin network, manages remote-access sessions, and drives the Pangolin API from the terminal — enabling zero-trust (ZTNA) access to internal services without exposing them to the public internet.

## Features

* Connect to a Pangolin server as a WireGuard-based VPN client
* Identity-aware, zero-trust remote access (ZTNA)
* Manage sites, tunnels and sessions from the command line
* Script Pangolin operations for automation and CI

## Package notes

This package installs the official Windows MSI from the [fosrl/cli](https://github.com/fosrl/cli) GitHub releases and is maintained automatically. It is not affiliated with or endorsed by Fossorial, Inc.</description>
